\b Basic Usage Instructions:
\b0 \
\
\cf4 Step 1 
\b Mac
\b0 :\cf0  Install the wizard application by opening the 
\i EasyRotator-Mac.dmg
\i0  disk image and running the installer inside the image.  The default installation settings should generally be used.\
\
\cf4 Step 1 
\b Windows
\b0 :\cf0  Install the wizard application by running the 
\i EasyRotator-Windows.exe
\i0  installer application.  The default installation settings should generally be used.\
\
\cf4 Step 2:\cf0  If you want to use the included Dreamweaver extension for easy access from within Dreamweaver, install the extension as follows:\
   - Launch Dreamweaver\
   - Select Help > Manage Extensions... to launch the Adobe Extension Manager  
\i [Note to users of old versions of Dreamweaver: If you don't see this option, you may need to manually launch the Macromedia Extension Manager.  Be sure to launch the version that corresponds to your Dreamweaver installation.]
\i0 \
   - Click the Install button in the Extension Manager.  Browse to and select the 
\i EasyRotator_DW_ext.mxp
\i0  file from this download package.\
   - Restart Dreamweaver after the extension installation is complete\
\
\cf4 Step 3:\cf0  If you're using the Dreamweaver Extension, you'll create rotators by opening a webpage in Dreamweaver and selecting 
\i Insert > DWUser > EasyRotator
\i0 .  You can make edits later by selecting a rotator in Design View and clicking the Edit button in the Properties panel.  If you're NOT using the Dreamweaver Extension, you'll create and edit rotators by simply launching the 
\i EasyRotator
\i0  application from your Programs or Applications menu.\
\
\

